# {{ project_name }}

> {{ project_description }}

Generated from [OpenProductKit](https://github.com/youruser/openproductkit) — a white-label product-template built around **one decoupled core** with thin web / CLI adapters.

## Architecture

```
packages/core        Pure Python domain models + Repository ports. No FastAPI, no DB, no HTTP.
apps/backend         FastAPI adapter. Owns SQLModel persistence (implements core ports).
apps/cli             Typer CLI + task runner ({{ cli_name }}).
apps/frontend        React + Vite web UI. Talks to the backend over HTTP.
```

Business logic lives only in `packages/core`. Everything else is a delivery mechanism.

## The demo: a small Resource Vault

Projects group notes; notes carry tags; you can search notes by project, tag or
free text. The same core services power the web API, the CLI and (later) the
desktop app.

```bash
# via the CLI adapter
uv run {{ cli_name }} project add "Research"
uv run {{ cli_name }} project list
uv run {{ cli_name }} note add <project-id> "Read paper" --tag ml --tag todo
uv run {{ cli_name }} note list --q paper
```

```
GET/POST /api/projects            list / create projects
GET      /api/projects/{id}       fetch a project
GET/POST /api/notes               search (?project_id=&tag=&q=) / create
GET      /api/notes/{id}          fetch a note
```

## Develop

```bash
